ont_size":12.5,"font_family":"Tahoma","font_color":16777215,"font_color_hex":"#ffffff","font_style":"Bold ","left":212.88582677165354,"top":68.05645669291339,"end_left":230.28574803149607,"end_top":344.1064566929134},{"original_text":"Beneï¬�t from Indiaâ€™s Growing Automotive Ecosystem.","font_size":12.5,"font_family":"Tahoma","font_color":16777215,"font_color_hex":"#ffffff","font_style":"Bold ","left":212.88582677165354,"top":68.05645669291339,"end_left":230.28574803149607,"end_top":344.1064566929134}]},"1":{"height":595.0,"width":420.0,"data":[{"original_text":"","font_style":"","left":0.9866141732283464,"top":0.0,"end_left":594.3366141732283,"end_top":419.35},{"original_text":"Growing per capita income and a young and growing working age population have contributed to India  becoming the 4th largest automobile market in the world in terms of domestic sales. Also, India ranks as  the 3rd largest automobile industry in the world in terms of production. The share of the automotive  sector to Indiaâ€™s GDP has risen to 7.1% as of February 2023 from a mere 2.8% in 1992! This growth has  also led to a positive spillover effect on the auto ancillary sector whose turnover has grown from US$","font_size":8.5,"font_family":"Arial MT","font_color":1381910,"font_color_hex":"#151616","font_style":"","left":74.70173228346457,"top":23.116771653543307,"end_left":151.25173228346455,"end_top":396.1667716535433},{"original_text":"39.05 billion in FY2016 to US$ 69.70 billion* in FY2023.","font_size":8.5,"font_family":"Arial MT","font_color":1381910,"font_color_hex":"#151616","font_style":"","left":74.70173228346457,"top":23.116771653543307,"end_left":151.25173228346455,"end_top":396.1667716535433},{"original_text":"*AutomoNve Component Manufacturers AssociaNon of India (ACMA), IBEF","font_size":7.0,"font_family":"Arial","font_color":1381910,"font_color_hex":"#151616","font_style":"Italic ","left":74.70173228346457,"top":23.116771653543307,"end_left":151.25173228346455,"end_top":396.1667716535433},{"original_text":"*AutomoNve Component Manufacturers AssociaNon of India (ACMA), IBEF","font_size":7.0,"font_family":"Arial","font_color":1381910,"font_color_hex":"#151616","font_style":"Italic ","left":74.70173228346457,"top":23.116771653543307,"end_left":151.25173228346455,"end_top":396.1667716535433},{"original_text":"OPPORTUNITIES IN THE INDIAN AUTOMOTIVE SECTOR","font_size":10.0,"font_family":"Arial","font_color":16777215,"font_color_hex":"#ffffff","font_style":"Bold ","left":42.508425196850396,"top":64.55370078740158,"end_left":56.508425196850396,"end_top":329.50370078740156},{"original_text":"OPPORTUNITIES IN THE INDIAN AUTOMOTIVE SECTOR","font_size":10.0,"font_family":"Arial","font_color":16777215,"font_color_hex":"#ffffff","font_style":"Bold ","left":42.508425196850396,"top":64.55370078740158,"end_left":56.508425196850396,"end_top":329.50370078740156},{"original_text":"KEY FACTORS - THE INVESTMENT POTENTIAL IN INDIAâ€™S  AUTOMOTIVE THEME","font_size":10.0,"font_family":"Arial","font_color":16777215,"font_color_hex":"#ffffff","font_style":"Bold ","left":173.42338582677166,"top":64.55314960629921,"end_left":199.42338582677166,"end_top":334.2531496062992},{"original_text":"KEY FACTORS - THE INVESTMENT POTENTIAL IN INDIAâ€™S  AUTOMOTIVE THEME","font_size":10.0,"font_family":"Arial","font_color":16777215,"font_color_hex":"#ffffff","font_style":"Bold ","left":173.42338582677166,"top":64.55314960629921,"end_left":199.42338582677166,"end_top":334.2531496062992},{"original_text":"Income Growth:","font_size":10.0,"font_family":"Trebuchet MS","font_color":1713487,"font_color_hex":"#1a254f","font_style":"Bold ","left":214.45496062992126,"top":81.48834645669291,"end_left":562.4549606299213,"end_top":391.08834645669293},{"original_text":"In the US, the number of cars per 1000 people is 860, in Germany it is 627 whereas in  China the number is 223. In contrast, India still has around 34 cars per 1000 people.","font_size":8.5,"font_family":"Arial MT","font_color":1381910,"font_color_hex":"#151616","font_style":"","left":214.45496062992126,"top":81.48834645669291,"end_left":562.4549606299213,"end_top":391.08834645669293},{"original_text":"Industry Growth Projections:","font_size":10.0,"font_family":"Trebuchet MS","font_color":1713487,"font_color_hex":"#1a254f","font_style":"Bold ","left":214.45496062992126,"top":81.48834645669291,"end_left":562.4549606299213,"end_top":391.08834645669293},{"original_text":"The automotive industry in India is projected to grow from $117 billion in 2023 to US$  188 billion by 2029 (Source: Mordor Intelligence). The auto components sector currently  stands at  US$ 71  billion  is expected to  reach $130  billion  by Fy29.  (Source: Ricardo Analysis).","font_size":8.5,"font_family":"Arial MT","font_color":1381910,"font_color_hex":"#151616","font_style":"","left":214.45496062992126,"top":81.48834645669291,"end_left":562.4549606299213,"end_top":391.08834645669293},{"original_text":"EV Market Evolution:","font_size":10.0,"font_family":"Trebuchet MS","font_color":1713487,"font_color_hex":"#1a254f","font_style":"Bold ","left":214.45496062992126,"top":81.48834645669291,"end_left":562.4549606299213,"end_top":391.08834645669293},{"original_text":"The EV (Electric Vehicle) market in India is forecasted to expand from $5.61 billion in  2023 to $37.7 billion by 2028, (Source: Mordor intelligence).","font_size":8.5,"font_family":"Arial MT","font_color":1381910,"font_color_hex":"#151616","font_style":"","left":214.45496062992126,"top":81.48834645669291,"end_left":562.4549606299213,"end_top":391.08834645669293},{"original_text":"Vehicle Credit Expansion:","font_size":10.0,"font_family":"Trebuchet MS","font_color":1713487,"font_color_hex":"#1a254f","font_style":"Bold ","left":214.45496062992126,"top":81.48834645669291,"end_left":562.4549606299213,"end_top":391.08834645669293},{"original_text":"As per RBI data, vehicle ï¬�nance is among the largest loan segments within retail and  commercial credit. The total vehicle loan book is around ` 15 trillion as on date, and it  is growing at mid-to-high teens over the last couple of years.","font_size":8.5,"font_family":"Arial MT","font_color":1381910,"font_color_hex":"#151616","font_style":"","left":214.45496062992126,"top":81.48834645669291,"end_left":562.4549606299213,"end_top":391.08834645669293},{"original_text":"Government Policies and Initiatives:","font_size":10.0,"font_family":"Trebuchet MS","font_color":1713487,"font_color_hex":"#1a254f","font_style":"Bold ","left":214.45496062992126,"top":81.48834645669291,"end_left":562.4549606299213,"end_top":391.08834645669293},{"original_text":"Policies like the Production Linked Incentive (PLI) scheme, 100% FDI allowance,  Automotive Mission Plan (AMP) 2016-26, Vehicle Scrappage Policy (Launched in  2021), and Faster Adoption and Manufacturing of Hybrid & Electric Vehicles (FAME)  scheme are expected to drive industry growth and innovation.","font_size":8.5,"font_family":"Arial MT","font_color":1381910,"font_color_hex":"#151616","font_style":"","left":214.45496062992126,"top":81.48834645669291,"end_left":562.4549606299213,"end_top":391.08834645669293},{"original_text":"Policies like the Production Linked Incentive (PLI) scheme, 100% FDI allowance,  Automotive Mission Plan (AMP) 2016-26, Vehicle Scrappage Policy (Launched in  2021), and Faster Adoption and Manufacturing of Hybrid & Electric Vehicles (FAME)  scheme are expected to drive industry growth and innovation.","font_size":8.5,"font_family":"Arial MT","font_color":1381910,"font_color_hex":"#151616","font_style":"","left":214.45496062992126,"top":81.48834645669291,"end_left":562.4549606299213,"end_top":391.08834645669293}]},"2":{"height":595.0,"width":420.0,"data":[{"original_text":"PERFORMANCE OF THE BENCHMARK","font_size":10.0,"font_family":"Arial","font_color":16777215,"font_color_hex":"#ffffff","font_style":"Bold ","left":41.79417322834646,"top":67.0603937007874,"end_left":55.79417322834646,"end_top":248.710393700787